Press cltr+alt+T
  
	sudo su

Check all available mongodb on your machine 

       sudo dpkg -l | grep mongo

Remove All mongoDB from your machine 

    sudo apt-get remove mongodb* --purge

Add Key

	sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 7F0CEB10

Add Sources List

	echo "deb http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu trusty/mongodb-org/3.2 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.2.list

Update your sources
	
	sudo apt-get update

Install mongodb-org

	sudo apt-get install mongodb-org

Check if working

	sudo systemctl status mongod

If not working
	
	sudo reboot

If still not working

	Run this script: enable_mongo.sh


reference link :::::::      http://askubuntu.com/questions/724749/install-mongo-3-2-on-ubuntu-15-10
